AN elderly farmer was shot dead in a shoot-out with cops in Bergville, in KwaZulu-Natal. It’s reported that Bergville police responded to a report of a shooting at a farm in Bergville. According to police spokesperson Brigadier Jay Naicker said it is alleged that the suspect shot a man who entered the farm, to collect his goats that were allegedly confiscated illegally. “The victim was taken to hospital for treatment after he was shot in the face,” Naicker said. Naicker added that police officers together with a hostage negotiator approached the 80-year-old suspect in an effort to arrest him for the attempted murder. The suspect allegedly opened fire at the police and was fatally wounded in the exchange of gunfire. He said the suspect’s firearm was seized following the shootout. “A case of attempted murder as well as an inquest docket was opened for further investigation,” Naicker said. 